The article announces several appointments made by the United States government. Monica M. Bertagnolli is appointed as the Director of the National Institutes of Health, replacing Francis S. Collins. Lisa DeNell Cook is appointed as a Member of the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System for a term of fourteen years, starting from February 1, 2024. Philip Nathan Jefferson is appointed as the Vice Chairman of the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System for a term of four years, replacing Lael Brainard. Adriana Debora Kugler is appointed as a Member of the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System to complete the unexpired term of fourteen years, starting from February 1, 2012, also replacing Lael Brainard. Jack A. Markell is appointed as the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Italian Republic and the Republic of San Marino. Nathalie Rayes is appointed as the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Croatia.